Credicorp, Femsa, Localiza: Latin America Equity Preview

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-03-11T10:17:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/credicorp-femsa-localiza-latin-america-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  The MSCI Latin America Index fell for a fourth day,
retreating 2.2 percent to 4,370.70.  Brazil    Localiza Rent a Car SA (RENT3)  (RENT3 BS): Latin America’s biggest
car-rental company had its rating raised to BB+ from BB at
Standard and Poor’s. The stock climbed 0.6 percent to 23.58
reais.    Mexico   Coca-Cola Femsa SAB (KOFL MM): The largest Coke bottler in
Latin America plans to sell debt in Mexico this year, the
company said in a statement to the Mexico stock exchange. The
company did not provide a date or size of the sale in the
statement. The stock slipped 0.4 percent to 90.94 pesos.  Peru    Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  : Peru’s largest financial services
company said it reached an agreement with  Carlyle Group  to start
a fund that will invest in private companies in  Peru . The fund
will start with capital of as much as $200 million, according to
a regulatory filing. The shares lost 0.3 percent to 105.95 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
